The paper uses mechanised reasoning to prove the soundness of an auction design, which falls under the category of automated reasoning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The auction design is combinatorial, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the use of formal methods, which is a topic in logic and verification (cs.LO). The auto-generation of verified executable code falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
